{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Problem\nRe-point the code_health metric specs at the analyzer + config instead of scanning `src/rebar/**/*.py` and `.github/module-size-limit.txt`, so a non-Python client gets honest Unavailable rather than fabricated zeros. Does NOT touch the CI module-size GATE (separate governance).\n\n## Per-metric post-migration semantics (G6)\n- `module_size_distribution`, `oversized_module_count`: compute from `AnalyzerResult [rebar:3b30-2168-ba16-41fc]`.loc plus `size_cap`/`size_near_fraction`, which come from the `[code_health]` config section created by prerequisite `[rebar:e7a0-acef-ec67-42bb]`, resolved onto the context object (read from `ctx`, no hardcoded file). `oversized_module_count` is today a seed stub (`_no_data_yet`); this ticket gives it a real compute.\n- `cap_change_events`: tracks edits to `.github/module-size-limit.txt` — a rebar-governance artifact with no client analogue. DEREGISTER the spec from the portable registry (remove from `register()`), documented in the close note.\n- `module_size_trend`: stays a seed stub returning **Unavailable** in THIS ticket. Wiring it to a real time series needs a scc-based snapshot WRITER that populates `{max_loc, over_cap_count}` records; no such writer exists, so it is OUT OF SCOPE / deferred to a follow-up ticket. (No trend-series reader is added here.)\n\n## Grounding (E4/G1G2 — verified)\n- CONFIRMED git_metrics.py: `_LIMIT_FILE` :35, `_read_cap` :75, scan root `src/rebar` :93, `cap_change_events` :167 registered ~:272.\n- Existing tests that pin the OLD behavior live at `tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py` and `tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics_heldout.py` (the `metrics/` subdirectory) and MUST be updated. `analyzer.py` is from `[rebar:3b30-2168-ba16-41fc]` (consumed, not created).\n\n## Acceptance criteria (observable + proving command)\n- [ ] No metric reader references the old hardcodes. PROVE: `! grep -Eq \"src/rebar|module-size-limit.txt\" src/rebar/metrics/git_metrics.py src/rebar/metrics/registry.py`.\n- [ ] Configured positive path: module_size_distribution / oversized_module_count return CORRECT values from a synthetic `AnalyzerResult [rebar:3b30-2168-ba16-41fc]` with known LOC (files at 100 and 850, cap 800 -> over_cap_count==1, max_loc==850). PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py::test_configured_positive`.\n- [ ] `cap_change_events` no longer registered. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py::test_cap_change_events_deregistered`.\n- [ ] `module_size_trend` returns Unavailable (no writer yet). PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py::test_trend_unavailable`.\n- [ ] Unconfigured analyzer -> Unavailable, NOT `{count:0,max_loc:0}` authoritative and NO leaked errno. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py::test_foreign_repo_honest_unavailable`.\n- [ ] git-delta (churn/refactor_ratio) + agent_process metrics unchanged; updated git_metrics tests green. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics_heldout.py`.\n\n## Dependencies: 3b30, 18f9, 21fb, 3ba0 (recorded depends_on edges).\n## Files likely touched\n- src/rebar/metrics/git_metrics.py, src/rebar/metrics/registry.py\n- tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py, tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics_heldout.py, tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py\n## Estimated scope: M\n\n## Compute-path mechanism (G6/T8/E4 — how AnalyzerResult reaches compute; loc shape; provenance)\n- `AnalyzerResult.loc` is the per-file LOC map + `max_loc` PRODUCED by the scc adapter `[rebar:18f9-5b75-b909-408c]` (this ticket depends_on it); compute reads `loc[<path>]` and `loc.max_loc`.\n- HOW the analyzer reaches compute: the module_size specs' `compute` resolves the analyzer via `resolve_analyzer` (from `[rebar:3b30-2168-ba16-41fc]`) using `ctx.repo_root` + the `[code_health]` config `[rebar:e7a0-acef-ec67-42bb]` (cap on `ctx`), obtains the `AnalyzerResult`, then counts. The existing `_spec` context adapter (which passes only `repo_root/since/until`) is EXTENDED to also resolve and pass the analyzer result. `ctx` attributes: `ctx.size_cap` and `ctx.size_near_fraction` (resolved from the `[code_health]` section).\n- PROVENANCE: the new/updated `module_size_distribution` and `oversized_module_count` `MetricSpec` entries carry `source=\"structural\"` (matching the existing seed specs).\n- [ ] the size specs resolve the analyzer + config and carry `source=\"structural\"`. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py::test_size_specs_provenance_and_resolve`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784600683769213001,"uuid":"a638fa2f-14f8-4ed3-a008-5543468f9512"}